# Creating Kali Template within Proxmox
1. Remove unique identifiers and system-specific data:
- Remove ssh host keys: sudo rm /etc/ssh/ssh_host_*
- Remove machine id: sudo rm /etc/machine-id
- Remove apt cache: sudo apt clean
2. Remove user-specific data:
- Remove user acc and data: sudo rm -r /home/*
  - Exit current terminal, if terminal command history still shows run
    - Clear terminal history: sudo history -c && history -w
3. Perform final system cleanup:
- Make sure QEMU guest agent is installed, if not run: sudo apt install qemu-guest-agent
- Make sure system is up-to-date: sudo apt upgrade && sudo apt full-upgrade -y
4. Make Template
- In Proxmox make sure VM is powered off
- Select VM and right click
- Click convert to template
